  "answer": {
    "why_dropping_v_did_not_make_the_old_run_lower_memory": "The original/native per-expert Muon path did halve persistent expert optimizer state, but it introduced rank-2 view/update/orthogonalization temporaries and slow Newton-Schulz work. The total training peak was also dominated by activations/backward memory, not just optimizer state.",
    "what_is_fixed": "The code now defaults expert-Muon to batched chunked expert-bank updates, uses local DTensor shards, and supports NS/chunk/state dtype knobs. Attention-only activation checkpointing avoids recomputing collective-bearing MoE.",
    "current_apples_to_apples_read": "At the same MBS8 attention-only shape, corrected Muon is lower-memory than AdamW by 16.82 GiB but slower by about 1.25% in the clean six-step run. The profile shows Muon's optimizer step is still about 4.9x AdamW's optimizer step at step 2, even with NS=1.",
    "decision": "Do not promote Muon as the current throughput path. Use AdamW MBS8 attention-only AC as throughput-best, keep MBS4 AdamW as lower-memory reference, and keep Muon only as a diagnostic memory branch unless a lower-level fused/distributed Muon update can remove the Newton-Schulz optimizer wall without NS=1 quality risk."
  }
